  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific laws targeting money laundering. In the United States, key anti-money laundering (AML) laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to report suspicious transactions, maintain records, and implement compliance programs to prevent money laundering. Internationally, organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) set global standards for combating financial crimes.",
